@@subheading GNU Pascal Drawing
@@cindex Drawing
@@cindex Blaise Pascal
@@cindex Pascal, Blaise

@@iftex
@@image{GnuPascal,6cm}
@@end iftex
@@ifhtml
Here is
@@end ifhtml
@@ifnothtml
On the web you can find
@@end ifnothtml
our GNU Pascal drawing as a
@@localuref{images/GnuPascal-small.png,small (1 KB)} and a
@@localuref{images/GnuPascal.png,large PNG image (10 KB)}, as an
@@localuref{images/GnuPascal.eps,EPS file (45 KB)}, and as a
@@localuref{images/GnuPascal.pdf,PDF file (18 KB)}.

Due to
@@uref{http://www.gnu.org/philosophy/gif.html,patent problems}
we do not use GIF files. Fortunately
@@uref{http://www.libpng.org,the PNG format}, the successor of GIF,
does not have this problem -- and introduces better compression and
more advanced features anyway.

@@c DEMO-START
@@anch{gradient}@@c
By the way, the @@localuref{images/gradient.png,color gradient} that makes
our page background is a PNG file of only 632 bytes. It was
generated by a Pascal program compiled with GPC and @@samp{pnmtopng}.
@@examplehref{gradient.pas}
@@c DEMO-END

